<div class="clearer"></div>
<div class="imageWithCaptionLeft" id="asset-46813">
<figure>
<img alt="A Tesla vehicle." src="/system/assets/0004/6813/121823_Tesla_Tesla.large.jpg?1702919216&amp;1702919216" title="A Tesla vehicle." />
<figcaption>
<p class="desc">The National Highway Traffic Safety Administration said Tesla will send out a software update to fix the problems.</p>
<p class="credit">Credit: Tesla</p>
</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<p>Tesla is recalling more than 2 million vehicles to fix Autopilot systems that the U.S. National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) determined did not have enough controls to prevent misuse.</p>
<p>The NHTSA said Tesla&rsquo;s method of ensuring drivers pay attention to the road while the driver-assistance system is activated is &ldquo;insufficient.&rdquo;</p>
<p>The agency has been investigating the software for more than two years in a probe examining more than a dozen crashes involving Teslas in Autopilot mode and parked emergency vehicles.<br/>
<br/>
From <em>The Washington Post </em><br/>
<a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2023/12/13/tesla-autopilot-recall/" target="_blank">View Full Article</a> - May Require Paid Subscription</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
